The International Fund for Animal Welfare says its especially appalling that a rhino orphanage has been attacked. JOHANNESBURG - The International Fund for Animal Welfare has condemned this week s attack at the Thula Thula Rhino Orphanage in KwaZulu-Natal where a rhino calf was killed and another severely injured.The welfare says while the details around the attack are sketchy, it appears security was breached by a gang of men who beat and brutalised staff before killing the calf.Animal welfare says its especially appalling that a rhino orphanage has been attacked. The welfare s Christina Pretorius said: Countries need to work together to put an end to this, as long as there is a market for rhino horn out there, we will continue to see this. 